   <mods:abstract>Chancery case involving James Duane's executors as trustees for Peter
            DuBois's creditors. Asks Peter to open packet with subscription papers for Memoirs of
            General Henry Lee. Attaches copy of his letter to the general's brother, Richard Bland
            Lee, concerning the project. Wants to promote the subscription as the Lees "have been
            constantly among my friends" and because general's treatment at Baltimore "should excite
            the Feelings of the Federalists." Suggests groups in New York that could help. Hopes to
            promote sales "not only from political motives, but because the Proceeds must be
            interesting to the General &amp; his family." Jay's note to Richard Bland Lee of
            September 12 follows, detailing Jay's interest in the forthcoming memoir and his
            indignation at "the Outrages committed at Baltimore."</mods:abstract>
